# Jhat Pat Game Rules

## Game State Machine
- `GameNotifier` is the single source of truth — no game logic outside it
- Phase transitions are one-way within a round: `showingPhoto → showingResultFlash → showingReveal`
- Only `GameNotifier` changes `GamePhase` — UI only reads it
- Timer is cancelled immediately on any answer (correct, wrong, or hint usage)
- `proceedToNextCard()` must reset: `eliminatedIndices`, `hintsUsed`, `isTimerFrozen`

## Scoring
- Points calculated only via `ScoringConstants.calculatePoints()` — no inline math
- Streak multiplier applied only via `ScoringConstants.applyStreakMultiplier()`
- Streak resets to 0 on wrong answer or timeout — never decrements
- Coins deducted before hint is applied — if deduction fails, hint does not apply

## Hints
- Max 1 eliminate hint per card, max 1 freeze hint per card
- Eliminate: keeps `correctAnswerIndex` option + 1 random wrong — removes the other 2
- Freeze: sets `isTimerFrozen = true` for exactly `ScoringConstants.freezeDurationSeconds`
- Eliminated tile indices stored in `GameState.eliminatedIndices` (Set<int>)
- Both hint buttons disabled once that hint type is used this card

## Session End
- `endSession()` called only once — guard against double calls
- Writes to Supabase happen in `endSession()`, never in the UI
- If Supabase write fails: save to Hive `pending_sessions` box, retry on next launch
- `levelUpProvider` set to true inside `profileProvider.awardXpAndCoins()` when level increases
- `levelUpProvider` reset to false only when user dismisses the level-up overlay
